  <body>
    <Navbar2 client:visible />
    <header>
      <div class="">
        <div class="absolute flex justify-center items-center w-full h-full">
          <a
            class="p-4 bg-accent rounded-xl text-white font-semibold hover:bg-accentdark"
            href="/">Go back to main version</a
          >
        </div>
        <img
          src="/NinaMadisonPlayingPiano.webp"
          class="w-full object-cover h-screen"
          alt="Nina Madison playing piano"
        />
      </div>
    </header>
  </body>
  <main>
    <section id="MusicPortfolio">
      <div class="container1000">
        <h2 class="p-2">music portfolio</h2>
        <iframe
          width="100%"
          height="600"
          scrolling="no"
          frameborder="no"
          tabindex="0"
          src="https://play.reelcrafter.com/embed/424662f2-4458-484d-b304-f608f2e839eb"
          class="rounded-lg"
        >
        </iframe>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section id="Credits">
      <div class="container1000">
        <h2>credits</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 grid-cols-1 gap-4">
          <div class="flex flex-col justify-start items-center">
            <h4>The lonely body - 2023</h4>
            <a
              href={lonelyBodyUrl}
              class="cursor-pointer transition ease-in-out delay-100 hover:opacity-80 hover:scale-105 shadow-image"
            >
              <Image src={TheLonelyBody} alt="The lonely body" height="500" />
            </a>
            <div class="flex flex-col justify-between p-4 md:p-8 h-full">
              <p class="italic">
                "Nina delivered a hauntingly brilliant score for The Lonely
                Body. She had an intuitive grasp of the material from the outset
                and was a joy to collaborate with leaving us with a score that
                far exceeded my expectations. I look forward to working with her
                again on my next film."
              </p>

              <a
                href="https://www.imdb.com/name/nm13635190/"
                class="flex justify-start items-center mt-8 mb-16 cursor-pointer group"
              >
                <Image
                  src={TimBrown}
                  width="80"
                  height="80"
                  alt="Tim Brown"
                  class="rounded-full mr-4"
                />
                <span class="group-hover:underline transition-all ease-in-out"
                  >Tim Brown / Director</span
                ></a
              >
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col justify-start items-center">
            <h4>La luce di Roma - 2021</h4>
            <a
              href={luceDiRomaUrl}
              class="cursor-pointer transition ease-in-out delay-100 hover:opacity-80 hover:scale-105 shadow-image"
            >
              <Image src={LaLuceDiRoma} alt="La luce di Roma" height="500" />
            </a>
            <div class="flex flex-col justify-between p-4 md:p-8 h-full">
              <p class="italic">
                "I chose Nina Madison's music because her melodies perfectly
                captured the spirit of our documentary. It's as if Nina, despite
                not fully knowing our narrative intentions, knew from the
                beginning where we wanted to take our audience and helped us
                achieve this with excellence. I find her music to be very
                evocative and persuasive, pulling at your heartstrings at the
                right moment.”
              </p>
              <a
                href="https://guidotalarico.com/"
                class="flex justify-start items-center mt-8 mb-16 cursor-pointer group"
              >
                <Image
                  src={GuidoTalarico}
                  width="80"
                  height="80"
                  alt="Guido Talarico"
                  class="rounded-full mr-4"
                />
                <span class="group-hover:underline transition-all ease-in-out"
                  >Guido Talarico / Director</span
                >
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="UpcomingProjects" class="!py-24">
          <h2>upcoming projects</h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 grid-cols-1 gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col h-full justify-between">
              <h4 class="text-left">
                Eternal Seas <br />
                <a
                  class="text-accent underline font-bold hover:text-white transition-all ease-in-out"
                  href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2124010/Eternal_Seas/"
                  >Versnel Studios</a
                >
              </h4>
              <p>
                Eternal Seas is an open world pirate RPG inspired by classic
                pirate games, set in a fictional island region. Command mighty
                vessels and lead your crew across the high seas and through lush
                jungles. Will you find fortune or will your soul be damned to
                sail the seas eternally?
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col h-full justify-between">
              <h4 class="text-left">
                'Spazio Vuoto' (Short, 2023/2024) <br />
                <a
                  class="text-accent underline font-bold hover:text-white transition-all ease-in-out"
                  href="https://www.instagram.com/brandolino_brandolini/"
                  >Brandolino Brandolini D'Adda</a
                > and <a
                  class="text-accent underline font-bold hover:text-white transition-all ease-in-out"
                  href="https://www.instagram.com/cosimo_desii/">Cosimo Desii</a
                >
              </h4>
              <p>
                Spazio Vuoto delves into the story of a young man returning home
                after his father's death. On this journey of self-discovery, he
                must confront the neglected relationship he had with his father
                and the memories of the home he grew up in, to finally move
                forward and live a life unburdened by the past.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="About" class="bg-white text-black -my-px">
      <div class="container1000">
        <h2 class="text-black">about</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6">
          <Image src={NinaBiographyImage} alt="Nina Madison" height="600" />
          <div class="flex flex-col w-full px-4 md:px-8">
            <h4 class="text-left">Biography</h4>
            <div class="flex flex-col space-y-3">
              <p>
                <strong>Nina Madison</strong> is an Italian composer for Film, TV,
                and Video Games. Her first collaboration was with writer and director
                <strong>Guido Talarico</strong> on his documentary <strong
                  >‘La Luce di Roma’ ('The Light of Rome')</strong
                >. Soon after she co-scored the music for the the horror short
                <strong>‘The Lonely Body’</strong>, directed by <strong
                  >Tim Brown</strong
                > and <strong>Jacob Dalton</strong>.
              </p>
              <p>
                She is currently collaborating as a co-composer on the upcoming
                video game <strong>‘Eternal Seas’</strong>, an open world
                pirate-themed RPG, creating a swashbuckling Mediterranean
                orchestral score. She is also working with director <strong
                  >Brandolino Brandolini D’Adda</strong
                > and <strong>Cosimo Desii</strong> to create a melodic piano and
                string score for their debut short
                <strong>‘Spazio Vuoto’ (Empty Space)</strong> .
              </p>
              <p>
                Nina attended the <strong>Screen Music Program</strong> in Pavia,
                Italy, where her teachers included composers <strong
                  >Carlos Rafael Rivera</strong
                > ("The Queen's Gambit, Griselda”) and <strong
                  >Garry Schyman</strong
                > (Bioshock, Dante’s Inferno). Her other mentors have included
                <strong>Christopher Young</strong> (Sinister, Spiderman 3), <strong
                  >Lennie Moore</strong
                > (Star Wars: The Old Republic, Halo: The Master Chief Collection),
                and five-time Emmy Award-winner <strong
                  >José Manuel Cancela</strong
                > (The Last Narc, Creed).
              </p>
              <p>
                Daughter of mixed-media artist <strong>Aldo Runfola</strong>,
                Nina grew up as an international traveller, studying classical
                piano in Berlin and voice in the UK, and is fluent in Italian,
                English, German, and Spanish. Being able to call more than one
                place <strong>‘home’</strong>, her identity always held roots
                in her creativity.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
